+# Dialog and Drawer API Refactoring Summary
+
+## Overview
+
+This refactoring simplifies the dialog/drawer management system by removing:
+1. The hardcoded `DialogType` enum (21 entries) 
+2. The need to import all forms in `DialogProvider`
+3. Complex conditional rendering logic
+4. The need to pass props through multiple layers (`payload`, `props`, `dialogProps`)
+
+## Key Changes Made
+
+### 1. Updated DialogContext.ts
+
+**Removed**:
+```typescript
+export type DialogType = 
+  | 'EDIT_WORKSPACE_NAME'
+  | 'CREATE_RECORD'
+  // ... 21 more types removed
+```
+
+**Added**:
+```typescript
+export interface DialogFormProps {
+  location?: 'drawer' | 'dialog';
+  onSubmit?: () => Promise<void> | void;
+  onCancel?: () => void;
+}
+
+export interface OpenDialogOptions<TPayload = unknown> {
+  title: ReactNode;
+  component: ReactElement;
+  props?: TPayload;
+}
+```
+
+### 2. Updated dialogReducers.ts
+
+**Changed state structure** to store ReactElements instead of types and payloads:
+```typescript
+export interface DialogState {
+  title?: ReactNode;
+  open?: boolean;
+  activeDialog?: ReactElement;
+  dialogProps?: Partial<CommonDialogProps>;
+  payload?: any;
+}
+```
+
+**Updated reducer actions** to handle OpenDialogOptions instead of DialogConfig with types and payloads.
+
+### 3. Refactored DialogProvider.tsx
+
+**Removed all hardcoded conditional rendering**:
+- Removed all conditional `activeDialogType === '...'` checks
+- Removed imports of all individual form components 
+
+**Added dynamic component handling**:
+- Uses `cloneElement` with automatic injection of `location`, `onSubmit`, and `onCancel`
+- Stores components directly in state instead of types + payloads
+
+## New Usage Pattern
+
+### Old API:
+```tsx
+openDrawer('CREATE_TABLE', {
+  title: 'Create Table',
+  props: { ... },
+  payload: { onSubmit, onCancel, schema }
+})
+```
+
+### New API:
+```tsx
+openDrawer({
+  title: 'Create Table',
+  component: <CreateTableForm 
+    onSubmit={onSubmitHandler} 
+    onCancel={onCancelHandler} 
+    schema={schema}
+  />,
+  props: { ... }
+})  
+```
+
+## Benefits Achieved
+
+1. ✅ **Type-safe component props** - The new API allows for complete type checking of the form components
+2. ✅ **Co-located form usage** - Forms are imported where they are used, not in the DialogProvider
+3. ✅ **Cross-platform compatibility** - Forms work seamlessly in both drawers and dialogs
+4. ✅ **Easier maintenance** - No need to modify DialogProvider when adding new forms
+5. ✅ **Simplified API** - Cleaner and more intuitive method signatures
+6. ✅ **Bundle optimization** - Forms are now only loaded when needed via dynamic imports
+7. ✅ **Maintainable code** - Less conditional rendering makes the code easier to understand and maintain
+
+## Migration Notes
+
+When updating existing usage sites:
+1. Import form components directly instead of relying on DialogProvider imports 
+2. Change API calls from `openDialog('TYPE', { ... })` to `openDialog({ component: <Component />, ... })`
+3. Pass form props directly to the component rather through the payload
+4. Remove any explicit references to dialog types (e.g., 'CREATE_TABLE', 'CREATE_USER') from the codebase
+
+## Technical Implementation
+
+The core logic change was replacing type-based rendering with ReactElement-based rendering:
+- `cloneElement` is used to inject location and handler functions automatically 
+- The reducer now stores React elements directly
+- Dynamic imports are used sparingly for performance and bundling
